It's actually forced,
so that's bad.

1519
01:19:13,050 --> 01:19:18,880
All right, one more
choice, this one.

1520
01:19:18,880 --> 01:19:21,894
If I do this together
with this one,

1521
01:19:21,894 --> 01:19:23,810
that's going to be bad
because that's a cycle.

1522
01:19:23,810 --> 01:19:26,860
We start and end at x.

1523
01:19:26,860 --> 01:19:29,430
What if I do this
one and that one?

1524
01:19:29,430 --> 01:19:30,930
Well, that's also
bad because here's

1525
01:19:30,930 --> 01:19:33,380
a cycle that starts
at x, ends at x.

1526
01:19:33,380 --> 01:19:36,040
This and this form the
inner of the cycle.

1527
01:19:36,040 --> 01:19:42,095
All cases are bad,
so no edge unfolding.

1528
01:19:42,095 --> 01:19:46,460

1529
01:19:46,460 --> 01:19:49,410
Tragic.

1530
01:19:49,410 --> 01:19:52,180
We can think briefly about
the case-- do I have time?

1531
01:19:52,180 --> 01:19:54,220
I have 10 seconds.

1532
01:19:54,220 --> 01:19:56,460
About the case where
there are two triangles.

1533
01:19:56,460 --> 01:20:01,460
I guess I should
draw them like this.

1534
01:20:01,460 --> 01:20:04,776
So this point is the
same as this point.

1535
01:20:04,776 --> 01:20:07,150
So if I try to simplify this,
instead of using four hats,

1536
01:20:07,150 --> 01:20:09,720
I just use two hats,
put one here, one here.

1537
01:20:09,720 --> 01:20:15,560
Then I could do something
like this, I think,

1538
01:20:15,560 --> 01:20:20,030
and maybe that's OK if
there's no cycle formed there.

1539
01:20:20,030 --> 01:20:22,740
So we really needed the
tetrahedron somehow.

1540
01:20:22,740 --> 01:20:25,580
I think it does work for
octahedron and larger also,

1541
01:20:25,580 --> 01:20:29,110
but just two triangles
is not enough.

1542
01:20:29,110 --> 01:20:32,375
And that is unfolding.

1543
01:20:32,375 --> 01:20:36,580
We did not always edge foldable
for general polyhedra, even

1544
01:20:36,580 --> 01:20:38,627
topologically convex polyhedra.

1545
01:20:38,627 --> 01:20:40,710
Next time, we'll talk more
about general unfolding

1546
01:20:40,710 --> 01:20:42,940
of arbitrary polyhedra.

